<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-07-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-07-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="1237" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1237">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.512/333.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Consul General <persName type="to">Hanna</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-07-15">
                                    <hi rend="italic">July 15, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your July 13. You say instructions have been sent to Gulf port
                            authorities to accept New York exchange in lieu of Mexican gold at
                            current rate of exchange, one for two.</p>
                        <pb facs="0866" n="750" xml:id="pg_750"/>
                        <p>Department does not understand what you mean by one for two, as current
                            rate of exchange is more like one for three. Please explain.</p>
                        <p>Will not General Carranza arrange that bar and other taxes may be paid in
                            Constitutionalist currency?</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>